> Cajun seasoning, lime, and fresh parsley give this salad a decidedly zesty feel. Sweet corn and tomato remind us how much we love July. Plus, what's better than a salad that can be served warm or cold? It's perfect for outdoor entertaining!

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 450 degrees. Cut the @sweet potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch cubes. In a #bowl{}, toss the cubes with the @Cajun spice blend{1%tablespoon}, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place on a #baking sheet{} in the oven for about ~{25%minutes}, tossing halfway through cooking, until golden brown.

Prep the remaining ingredients: Cut the corn kernels of the @corn on the cob{1}. Halve, peel, and finely dice half the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and finely diced). Zest, then halve the @lime{1}. Halve the @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Drain and rinse the @kidney beans{1%box}. Finely chop the @parsley{¼%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add the corn and red onion and cook, tossing for ~{2-3%minutes}, until softened. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the kidney beans and tomatoes and toss for another ~{1%minute}, until heated through. Season with salt and pepper. Remove the pan from the heat, then stir in the lime zest, lime juice, and parsley.

When the potatoes are done, toss them into the pan with the corn mixture along with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and the @feta cheese{½%cup}. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Plate: Serve divided between bowls and enjoy!